# ── Form email delivery via Resend (required) ─────────────────────────────────
# All site forms (Hero "Book Your Inspection", Contact "Get a Free Quote", and
# the service-page shield form) POST to the Vercel serverless function
# /api/contact, which verifies the reCAPTCHA token and emails the lead through
# Resend. These are SERVER-side secrets — do NOT prefix them with VITE_ (that
# would expose them in the browser bundle). Set them in the Vercel dashboard
# (Project → Settings → Environment Variables); for local `vercel dev`, put them
# in a local .env file.
#
#   1. Create an account at https://resend.com and add + verify your domain.
#   2. Create an API key → paste it as RESEND_API_KEY.
#   3. RESEND_FROM must use your verified domain.
#
RESEND_API_KEY=
RESEND_FROM=Preventive Home Solutions <noreply@yourdomain.com>
RESEND_TO=Preventivehomeservices@gmail.com

# ── Google reCAPTCHA v2 checkbox ("I'm not a robot") — required ────────────────
# Create keys at https://www.google.com/recaptcha/admin
#   → reCAPTCHA type: "Challenge (v2)" → "I'm not a robot Checkbox"
#   → add your domain(s) (and localhost for local testing)
# The SITE key is public and MUST be prefixed VITE_ so the client can render the
# checkbox. The SECRET key is server-side only (no VITE_ prefix).
#
VITE_RECAPTCHA_SITE_KEY=
RECAPTCHA_SECRET_KEY=

# ── Live Google reviews (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the two values to pull REAL reviews from
# the Preventive Home Solutions Google Business Profile. Without them, the site
# shows representative fallback reviews (the marquee still scrolls either way).
#
# 1. VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY
#    - Google Cloud Console → enable "Places API (New)" + Maps JavaScript API
#    - Billing must be enabled on the project
#    - Restrict the key by HTTP referrer (your domain) before going to production
#
# 2. VITE_GOOGLE_PLACE_ID
#    - Find it with Google's "Place ID Finder":
#      https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/place-id
#
# Note: Google's API returns at most 5 reviews per business — that is a hard
# limit on Google's side, not a limitation of this code.

VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
VITE_GOOGLE_PLACE_ID=
